<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08184m"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08184m">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08184m"> 184(m)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> waxed tablets</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> In lona Adamnan took down hastily on waxed tablets, and then copied out fairly on parchment, the experiences of Asculf, a Gaulish bishop, who had lived for nine months in the Holy Land. So was knowledge preserved for the community, and we still have this description of Jerusalem written in the seventh century. <small> Stephen Gwynn, <a name="SGHI" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SGHI"><cite title="source">The History of Ireland</cite></a> (1923) 39</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
